<hl>
<seg id=1> Fei Xiaotong Awarded Magcycy Award </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency. Manila. Aug. 31. (Reporter Xiong Changyi) The China's renowned socialist and vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the NPC, Dr Fei Xiaotong was awarded here this afternoon the 1994 Magsaysay Award for "Community Leadership". </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The award-presenting ceremony was held solemnly at the Philippine Culture Center. </seg>
<seg id=4> The Philippine president Ramos attended the award-presenting ceremony and gave out the medal,bonus and certificate to the six distinguished figures who were honoredly awarded this year's Magsaysay Award. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> Fei Xiaotong, while delivering his thanking address, said, "I won't fail to live up to the encouragement given by our fridently neighboring country; no matter how many years and months available are left for me, I will have to conscientiously make use of every single minute, trying to do some good deeds that are beneficial to the Asian people and even the people all over the world, which in turn will make it possible that the knowledge accumulated by man plays the role of driving the society to develop into a better one." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> The Ramen-Magsaysay Award named after the former Philippine president is dubbed as Asia's Nobile Prize. </seg>
<seg id=7> The award, consisting of five fields, is awarded annually and respectively to individuals and bodies that have made outstanding contributions in such fields as government service, public service, community leadership, journalism and literature, creative exchange art and international understanding. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> The award, since its debut in 1958, has gone to 172 individuals and 14 bodies. </seg>
</p>
